ctionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Lincolnshire was born in 1165, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Alfigifu Malet. He died in 1218, in his hometown, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1165–1218":"1165–1218","1045–1100":"1045–1100","1155–1218":"1155–1218","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1045":"1045","1165":"1165","1218":"1218","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1165–1218":"1165–1218","1045–1100":"1045–1100","1155–1218":"1155–1218","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1045":"1045","1165":"1165","1218":"1218","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1165–1218":"1165–1218","1045–1100":"1045–1100","1155–1218":"1155–1218","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1045":"1045","1165":"1165","1218":"1218","England":"Angleterre","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William de Lincolnshire est né en 1165, à Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Alfigifu Malet. Il est décédé en 1218, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 53 ans."},"de":{"1165–1218":"1165–1218","1045–1100":"1045–1100","1155–1218":"1155–1218","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","